âœ… 1. You are binding twice â€” client template + popup editor conflict

Inside your popup editor you already have:

@(Html.Kendo().MultiSelect()
    .Name("VehicleSeriesEditor")
    .Value(Model.BusId)
)


But then you inject your client template:

VehicleSeriesEditor.cshtml

Which ALSO creates:

.Name("rbmultiselect")


âž¡ï¸ Now the widget that Kendo initializes is rbmultiselect, not VehicleSeriesEditor,
and VehicleSeriesEditor never gets a Kendo widget attached â†’ meaning no DataSource â†’ no Read() call.

This is a classic Telerik popup-template issue.

âœ… 2. Your popup template MultiSelect has no DataSource

Your popup editor uses:

@(Html.Kendo().MultiSelect()
    .Name("VehicleSeriesEditor")
    .Value(Model.BusId)
)


But it does not include:

.DataSource(...)
.DataTextField(...)
.DataValueField(...)


âž¡ï¸ So when the popup shows, the MultiSelect exists, but it has no configuration â†’ Kendo ignores it and instead uses the client template.

âœ… 3. .Value("BusId") in template is wrong

This:

.Value("BusId")


Should only be used if you literally pass a list of IDs, like:

.Value(new[] { 1, 2, 3 })


Using "BusId" as a string makes Kendo think you're passing a preselected value "BusId" (literal text), not a field.

ðŸŽ¯ BEST PRACTICE FIX â€” Only define the MultiSelect in ONE place
Inside popup editor partial _RbPopUpEditor.cshtml

Replace your MultiSelect with the full widget config:

@(Html.Kendo().MultiSelect()
    .Name("VehicleSeriesEditor")   // Name MUST match model binding
    .DataTextField("BusName")
    .DataValueField("BusId")
    .Placeholder("Select Vehicle..")
    .Filter("contains")
    .AutoBind(true)
    .Value(Model.BusId != null ? new[] { Model.BusId } : null)
    .DataSource(ds =>
    {
        ds.Read(read => read.Action("ReadBuses", "RebuiltParts"));
    })
)

And remove VehicleSeriesEditor.cshtml OR stop including it in the popup template.
ðŸŽ¯ If you want to keep the client template, then remove the MultiSelect from _RbPopUpEditor.cshtml

Your popup should contain ONLY:

<div class="form-group double-width">
    @Html.Label("BusId", "Vehicle Series")
    @(Html.Partial("VehicleSeriesEditor"))
</div>


And inside VehicleSeriesEditor.cshtml:

@(Html.Kendo().MultiSelect()
    .Name("BusId")
    .DataTextField("BusName")
    .DataValueField("BusId")
    .Placeholder("Select Vehicle..")
    .Filter("contains")
    .BindTo(Model)
    .DataSource(ds =>
    {
        ds.Read(r => r.Action("ReadBuses", "RebuiltParts"));
    })
)


IMPORTANT:
The name must match your model property (BusId) so the Grid binds it correctly.
